Oke, saya buat langkah demi langkah supaya kamu paham COPY --from=builder itu bekerja bagaimana.

1. Buat folder project

Di PowerShell:

mkdir belajar-docker
cd belajar-docker
2. Buat package.json
notepad package.json

Isi:

{
  "name": "my-node-app",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "server.js",
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^5.1.0"
  }
}

Kenapa pakai express?
Supaya node_modules benar-benar dibuat.

Save.

3. Install dependency (node_modules)

Di terminal:

npm.cmd install

Ini akan membuat:

node_modules/
package-lock.json

Cek:

dir
4. Buat server.js
notepad server.js

Isi:

const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello Rahmat!');
});

app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'healthy' });
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});

Save.

5. Buat Dockerfile
notepad Dockerfile

Isi:

# Stage 1: Builder
FROM node:20-alpine AS builder

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./

RUN npm install

# Stage 2: Final image
FROM node:20-alpine

WORKDIR /app

# Salin node_modules dari builder
COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules

# Salin source code
COPY . .

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["node", "server.js"]
6. Cara kerja COPY --from=builder

Saat build:

Stage 1 (builder)

Docker menjalankan:

RUN npm install

Hasilnya:

/app/node_modules

berisi package express.

Stage 2

Docker menjalankan:

COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules

Artinya:

ambil folder:
/app/node_modules

dari stage:
builder

copy ke:
./node_modules

jadi image final tidak perlu install ulang dependency.

7. Build image
docker build -t my-node-app .
8. Jalankan container
docker run -p 3001:3000 my-node-app

Buka browser:

http://localhost:3001

Health:

http://localhost:3001/health

Ini contoh yang 100% cocok untuk memahami COPY --from=builder.
